DrScheme for DEBIAN
----------------------

This is a Scheme environment originally created by the Computer Science
department at Rice University, and now maintained by the PLT project
(a group of former Rice faculty and students spread across a range of
Universities and professional organizations.)

DrScheme consists of a graphical environment (under X) with emacs-style
keybindings.  It provides various levels of "strictness" with respect to
its parsing of Scheme so that beginners can be presented with more specific
error messages than a standard Scheme environment.

The how's and why of DrScheme are discussed in a paper available
on-line at: http://www.plt-scheme.org/software/drscheme.

The homepage is at: http://www.plt-scheme.org/software/drscheme.

