NOTES:

1.  You should place any PLT packages not under the control of dkg
in ~/.plt-scheme.  Otherwise, they may be overwritten on your next upgrade.

2.  A note on naming schemes:

Stable releases are ### (e.g., 206)
Urgent patched releases are ###p# (e.g., 206p1)

3.  Web Server

To start the web server at boot time (on port 8000 by default), modify the
/etc/default/mzscheme file to say "RUN_HTTPD=Yes", rather than the default
"RUN_HTTPD=No."  The post install script does this automatically if you answer
the debconfig web server question in the affirmative.
